  "prompt": "Why haven't we seen Jack Nicholson in any film lately?",
  "response": "Jack Nicholson, one of the most iconic actors in Hollywood, has been notably absent from the screen in recent years. The primary reason for his absence appears to be his semi-retirement from acting. Nicholson, who was born in 1937, has had an illustrious career spanning several decades, with numerous acclaimed performances in films such as *One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest*, *The Shining*, *Chinatown*, and *As Good as It Gets*. \n\nHere are some key factors that may explain his absence:\n\n1. **Retirement or Semi-Retirement**: Nicholson has effectively stepped back from acting since 2010, following his role in *How Do You Know*. While he has not officially announced his retirement, he has indicated in interviews that he is content with his career and is enjoying his time away from the spotlight.\n\n2. **Age and Health**: At 86 years old (as of 2023), Nicholson may be prioritizing his health and personal life. While there have been no confirmed reports of serious health issues, it\u2019s not uncommon for actors of his age to slow down or retire.\n\n3. **Selective About Roles**: Nicholson has always been known for being highly selective about the roles he takes on. He has stated that he only chooses projects that truly inspire him. It\u2019s possible that no recent scripts have met his standards or piqued his interest enough to return to acting.\n\n4. **Focus on Personal Life**: Nicholson has been spending more time with family and friends, and enjoying his private life. He is also an avid basketball fan and has been a regular attendee at Los Angeles Lakers games.\n\nWhile fans of Jack Nicholson may miss seeing him on screen, it\u2019s clear that he has earned the right to take a step back and enjoy his life after decades of remarkable contributions to cinema.",
